Royal Emirates May Buy Spain’s Getafe Soccer Club, FT Reports

-- B y   A l a n   P u r k i s s
-- 
2011-04-20T04:51:52Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-04-20/royal-emirates-may-buy-spain-s-getafe-soccer-club-ft-reports.html
Royal Emirates Group, owned by
Sheikh Butti bin Suhail al-Maktoum, a member of Dubai’s ruling
family, may announce tomorrow that it’s buying Getafe, a soccer
club in La Liga,  Spain ’s top league, the Financial Times
reported, citing Royal Emirates.  The company declined to confirm or deny that the club to be
bought is Getafe and the club refused to comment, the newspaper
reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Alan Purkiss in  London  on   apurkiss@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Colin Keatinge at 
 ckeatinge@bloomberg.net . 